timing_report_...int_loop_check(25.10)  timing_report_...int_loop_check(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_skip_constraint_loop_check

Syntax
       timing_report_skip_constraint_loop_check

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Allows you to skip loop checking when the check_timing command is used.

       When  set  to  true,  the software skips reporting of loops in case the
       timing graph inside a loop is broken. This may happen if  some  of  the
       commands,  such  as, create_clock, set_input_delay, or set_output_delay
       are defined inside a loop.

       Note: When this global variable is set to true, the  check_timing  com-
       mand   will   report  lesser  loops  than  the  ones  reported  in  the
       CTE_loops.rpt report - which reports all the loops.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

